  "riddle": "1. Seek the page that chronicles a remarkable year for gymnastics, where a Canadian city hosted an unforgettable competition. What year saw the last games before this event?\n\n2. A grand showcase unfolded across multiple tongues — how many languages shared the tale of these athletic accomplishments?\n\n3. In the binary realm of your recent discovery, how many 1-bits can you find in that number's representation?\n\n4. Look for the athlete who vaulted onto the world stage during these games, representing a discipline defined by grace and strength. Which type of gymnastics did he practice?\n\n5. A realm of moving images connects us all — how many languages are available to explore this medium's grand narrative?\n\n6. Venture into the history of the channel known for its live coverage of many athletic contests. In what year did it first come into existence?\n\n7. With a twist of digits, what number emerges if you reverse the establishment year of this broadcasting giant?\n\n8. Discerning the launch of the sports division, can you find out when this network began its focus on athletic events?\n\n9. With coordinates pointing to a bustling business center, what string of numbers represents this famous locale's latitude and longitude?\n\n10. At what height does the vibrant heart of this district lie above sea level? Seek the altitude at which this part of the city resides.\n\n11. How many hotels cater to visitors in the vicinity of this thriving location? Count the lodging available for weary travelers.\n\n12. Gather the results from your earlier elevation discovery and the nearby hotel tally. What sum do you derive from those numbers?\n\n13. Seek the count of sacred spaces that grace the intersection of Sixth Avenue and 42nd Street. How many churches stand in this area?\n\n14. The pathway that runs through the city embraces its length. What measurement is officially recorded for this avenue of commerce and culture?\n\n15. Look into the city's heights once more, this time for the elevation of the avenue named after the Americas. What altitude does it claim?\n\n16. How many medical sanctuaries can you find near this same thoroughfare? Tally the hospitals that serve those in need.\n\n17. Combine the altitude where this avenue lies with your recent count of hospitals. What total do you yield from these two numbers?\n\n18. Now, shift your focus to a country that recently competed in global athletic endeavors. What is the population of that land?\n\n19. Finally, as the curtain closes on this quest, compute the digital root of the sum derived from clues 6, 13, and 15. This final answer will reveal the essence of your journey, boiling down to a single digit between 0 and 9.",
